node.text: The new album is named for West’s late mother, who passed away in 2007. While DONDA explores a wider range of genres than his previous album Jesus is King, it features some of the religious themes that West has pivoted to in his recent music. A partial tracklist posted by West ahead of the release listed titles like “Pure Souls” and “Keep My Spirit Alive.” The album will be available for purchase and streaming on July 23rd.

node.text: Founded by Jeff Bezos, space travel company Blue Origin completed its first passenger flight on July 20. The rocket, named New Shepard, carried Bezos and three other passengers more than 65-miles above Earth, just to the boundary of space, known as the Kármán line. Watch our latest episode of HBNN to learn more.

node.title: @jeffbezos Completes His First Flight into Space

@hypebeastcarclub: @lamborghini Seoul has unveiled the Aventador S Roadster “Korean Special Series,” which is comprised of two unique V12 supercars that are inspired by South Korea‘s rich culture and history. The first arrives in “Green Ocno,” described as being a symbol of “warm Korean sentiment.” It's fitted with black wheels and a graphic pattern paired with a “Bianco Leda” interior. Moving on to the incredibly rare “Blue Emera” version, the supercar represents “intelligence and wisdom,” boasting contrasting graphics and the “Bianco Leda” interior. Hit the link in bio for more info.⁠⁠
Photo: Lamborghini

node.text:
@hypeart: The ancient Roman Thermopolium (fast food bar) that was first excavated by archaeologists in 2019, is now open for the public’s viewing. The site, which was consumed by ash in 79 A.D. is located at Pompeii’s Regio V site and is remarkably well-preserved — full of frescoes and still lifes, such as a Nereid riding a horse. Hit the link in bio for more. ⁠⁠
Photo: @luigi.spina.photographer/Pompeii Sites

node.text:
@hypebeastwatches: @audemarspiguet has quietly released another 150 pieces of its titanium salmon dial Royal Oak Perpetual Calendar for the global market. Originally a Japan exclusive, the limited-edition timepiece features a perpetual calendar function powered by the calibre 5134, a full titanium case and bracelet, an astronomical moon phase, week indicator, and a salmon Grande Tapisserie dial. It’s available now for $85,100 USD.⁠⁠
Photo: Audemars Piguet
